  "title": "`<div data=\"[object Object]\">` in 1.3.0",
  "body": "I just moved from 1.2 to 1.3, and I realize that my markup now have a lot of `data=\"[object Object]\"` while inspecting with the Chrome inspector. This has no side effect that I can currently see, but this seems like something that shouldn't be visible in the markup.\n## 1.3\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/13556164/455a9860-e3d3-11e5-9a1a-87375c8e6c5b.png)\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/13556167/53efbd74-e3d3-11e5-8473-efa083a85470.png)\n## 1.2.5\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/13556177/7b355b78-e3d3-11e5-9776-bb86de0c9edc.png)\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/13556170/5fbc7eb2-e3d3-11e5-876f-37f16fc7e488.png)\n",
